post_text:
The Lake Preston Student Council is hosting a dodgeball tournament on Friday, March 6th from 2pm until 3:30pm in the Main Gym. The tournament is to raise money to purchase a water bottle filling station for the elementary. Parents and community members are welcome to come cheer on our teams. Spectators are asked to make a free will donation of $1.00 to help us meet our goal. Should you wish to make a free will donation without attending the tournament, please contact the school directly.

Limited concessions will be available for purchase for the middle school and high school throughout the tournament. Please do not send money for concessions with your elementary student; however money for the free will donation would be welcome.

Our tournament will consist of ten games. We have four MS/HS teams and one Staff team 

post_text: State Tournament wrestling ticket information: First of all we are 8th in the power point rankings for qualifying for the State Dual Tournament. The top 8 qualify. With that being said the only way our fans can guarantee sitting all together as a team group is to purchase tickets by Thursday of this week. Reserved tickets for the tournament cost $50. Tickets need to be paid for with checks written out to Arlington Public Schools, by Thursday at noon on Jan. 30. Student tickets are all general admission. Tickets can be purchased for individual sessions at the tournament, however those tickets may not be in the Kingsbury Knight fan section. Let me know if you have any questions. Mr. Gilbertson
